HOUSE of Zwide actress Winnie Ntshaba has praised actor Vusi Kunene for his leading role. Winnie (47), who plays the role of Faith Zwide, the wife to rich businessman Funani Zwide, played by Vusi, couldn’t get enough of how he executed his character. The e.tv soapie, that airs from Monday to Friday at 7pm, has left viewers sad as they want Funani to finally know the truth about his wife. This drama unfolded on the latest episode, where Funani was seen getting closer to the truth about his stolen baby, Ona. And on Tuesday, 12 July, Winnie shared that she felt honoured to be acting alongside the legendary actor. ALSO READ : Trevor’s brillant show bags seven Emmy nominations! “What an honour to be able to play and tell this story with the legend. I salute you and I thank you,” she wrote on social media. The actress also shared that he gave her a look that made her even forget that she was in character. “But the look you gave Faith today made me even shiver, kuyashuba manje. Ziyakhala ziku loud speaker,” she added. A post shared by Bawinile Ntshaba (@winnie_ntshaba) 